  "response": "The first smartphone in the world is widely recognized as the IBM Simon Personal Communicator. It was developed by IBM and introduced in 1992, and it became available for purchase in 1994. The IBM Simon combined the features of a mobile phone with those of a PDA (Personal Digital Assistant), including a touchscreen, calendar, address book, and other functions that are common in smartphones today.",
